      "content": "interesting. you called it a success because it toppled an adversary, but can you really call an operation a \"success\" if it basically destroyed the state and led to years of civil war and a massive power vacuum? wouldn't a realist argue that the long-term instability actually made the region more dangerous for US interests in the long run?",
